positionList.description:
- Developed new tool to streamline inter-agency creative wearout calculation process;
- Maintained and actualized total media budget; prepared, issued, and recorded all buy authorizations and schedules;
- Responsible for research, analysis, and presentation of national sports & sponsorship opportunities.

As Implementation Executive:
- Responsible for overall install success, customer satisfaction, and internal team performance on three concurrent electronic medical record (EHR) implementation projects on the East Coast;
- Experience with large, integrated delivery networks and academic medical centers, budgets up to $150 milion USD

As Team Lead Manager:
- Directly supervise ~15 team members, including other team leads (managers);
- Head manager of core leadership group for a team of approximately 200;
- Staffing and personnel manager: responsible for customer placements, career path planning, and performance for 200 implementation staff;
- Other internal responsibilities: recruiting and interviewing; training orientation and role-specific classes.

As People Manager:
- Directly responsible for staff happiness, growth, performance, and retention for a team of 200+;
- Member of leadership group responsible for overall culture and happiness for a division of 2,000+;
- Improved retention of top performers by 43% from 2013 to 2014, and by 15% between 2014 and 2015.

As Boost Practice Lead:
- Part of senior management team responsible for capacity planning, new business development, process improvement of Epic’s newest, largest division (300+ remote consultants, 50 managers, $80 million+ annual revenue)
- Created new processes for expediting contracting, and defined and developed documentation on role expectations, benefits, and performance

As Implementation Director: 
- Led on time, on-budget implementation of outpatient and inpatient clinical and revenue cycle applications for two NYS healthcare networks, managing install teams ranging in size from 2-25.

As Team Lead:
- Directly supervised 15+ team members (non-managers); 
- Member of core leadership group for a team that grew from 80 to 200+ members within 2 years;
- Staffing manager, responsible for customer placements for all implementation staff.

- Led successful ADT install for large Midwestern community hospital system;
- In addition to technically-focused work, volunteered for process improvement and personnel coordination tasks: managed integrated dress rehearsals and designed and implemented go-live cutover plan;
- Won award for most outstanding performance during the second phase of the install (design/validation).

Internal specialist in ROI, healthcare cashflow pathways, data management, and developing implementation methodologies, tools, and dashboards.
